# <Project> — Project Memory

## Workflow rules (non-negotiable)
- Capture a spec (`docs/spec.md`) before the plan for non-trivial work; the plan derives from it.
- Never implement before the human approves the plan.
- The PM orchestrates and does not write code — implementation is done by subagents.
- Every story traces to requirement IDs (FR-/AC-); run `/pm-skill:analyze` before implementation on non-trivial projects.
- Log progress to `pm/log.md` (append-only, author-prefixed entries) after every meaningful step.
  `pm/` is git-tracked — commit state updates with the work they describe; your position lives in
  `pm/actors/<your-id>.json` and you never edit another actor's file; never write secrets into
  `pm/` (`tmp/` is scratch and stays gitignored).
- The project's gates (test/lint/build) must pass, and `pm-verifier` must return PASS, before a story ships.
- Never push to a remote without an explicit request.

